WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.235 --> 00:00:02.669
MALE NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> Grimm.

2
00:00:02.736 --> 00:00:03.829
Aunt Marie?

3
00:00:03.904 --> 00:00:06.965
The misfortune of our family
is already passing to you.

4
00:00:07.140 --> 00:00:10.167
<i>We have the ability to
see what no one else can.</i>

5
00:00:10.677 --> 00:00:12.043
You are one of the last Grimms.

6
00:00:12.846 --> 00:00:14.007
What did you say you were?

7
00:00:14.248 --> 00:00:15.443
"Blutbad."

8
00:00:15.582 --> 00:00:18.484
<i>Vulgarized by your ancestors
as the "Big Bad Wolf."</i>

9
00:00:18.819 --> 00:00:19.843
You.

10
00:00:21.255 --> 00:00:22.780
(BOTH GRUNTING)

11
00:00:24.658 --> 00:00:26.957
MARIE: <i>When they lose
control they can't hide</i>

12
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:29.622
<i>and we see them for
what they really are.</i>

13
00:00:29.696 --> 00:00:31.358
NICK: <i>Is she dead?</i> DR. ROSE: <i>No.</i>

14
00:00:31.431 --> 00:00:32.626
<i>He was there.</i>

15
00:00:33.133 --> 00:00:34.293
We'll just have to try again.

16
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.074
Tired of searching for subtitles?
Ray generates them instantly: getray.app

17
00:00:56.356 --> 00:00:57.847
(BOTH PANTING)

18
00:01:32.426 --> 00:01:33.450
Oh!

19
00:01:34.561 --> 00:01:36.223
Nirvana!

20
00:01:39.032 --> 00:01:40.056
Oh!

21
00:01:40.734 --> 00:01:42.600
Why weren't we born rich?

22
00:01:42.669 --> 00:01:45.400
'Cause our parents
didn't have any money.

23
00:01:46.306 --> 00:01:47.330
Hmm.

24
00:01:51.678 --> 00:01:53.078
Shall we go on
our yacht. darling?

25
00:01:53.146 --> 00:01:54.478
Which one?

26
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:02.384
(GLASS SHATTERING)

27
00:02:02.456 --> 00:02:03.981
(BOTH LAUGHING)

28
00:02:05.425 --> 00:02:07.326
Slow down. Oh. you wish.

29
00:02:12.265 --> 00:02:13.597
Gilda?

30
00:02:14.901 --> 00:02:18.303
Where do you think you're going?

31
00:02:24.444 --> 00:02:25.639
(GILDA SCREAMING)

32
00:02:25.712 --> 00:02:27.237
(BOTH LAUGHING)

33
00:02:33.220 --> 00:02:34.984
Catch me if you can.

34
00:02:36.857 --> 00:02:37.950
Oh. I can.

35
00:02:41.261 --> 00:02:43.025
Gilda? Come on.

36
00:02:45.432 --> 00:02:47.162
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

37
00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.190
What was that? What?

38
00:03:17.264 --> 00:03:18.630
I think I heard a car.

39
00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:19.860
No. you didn't.

40
00:03:20.067 --> 00:03:22.901
Rocky! Stop! Go
look out the window.

41
00:03:23.103 --> 00:03:25.004
What. now? Yeah. Go!

42
00:03:29.076 --> 00:03:32.171
Somebody's here. You're
right. Come on. Let's go.

43
00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:33.645
(CHUCKLING)

44
00:03:33.814 --> 00:03:36.249
Oh! No. no. not the
door. The window.

45
00:03:36.316 --> 00:03:37.545
Come on.

46
00:03:37.617 --> 00:03:39.210
(GILDA LAUGHING)

47
00:03:39.453 --> 00:03:40.819
ROCKY: Shh!

48
00:03:42.189 --> 00:03:44.158
(LAUGHING) ROCKY: Got it.

49
00:03:44.624 --> 00:03:45.956
(GRUNTING)

50
00:03:47.861 --> 00:03:49.887
You okay? Yeah. I'm fine.

51
00:03:51.431 --> 00:03:54.595
(GROANING) Come
on. Let's go. Hurry up!

52
00:03:55.102 --> 00:03:56.263
(EXCLAIMS)

53
00:03:58.371 --> 00:04:00.033
Rocky. what are you doing?

54
00:04:00.173 --> 00:04:01.641
(ROCKY SCREAMING)

55
00:04:01.708 --> 00:04:03.301
(ROCKY GRUNTING)

56
00:04:04.611 --> 00:04:06.011
(LOUD GROWL)

57
00:04:07.013 --> 00:04:08.345
(ROCKY SCREAMING)

58
00:04:12.719 --> 00:04:14.051
(GROWLING)

59
00:04:15.122 --> 00:04:17.114
(GILDA BREATHING HEAVILY)

60
00:04:23.497 --> 00:04:25.022
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

61
00:04:25.098 --> 00:04:26.464
Come on.

62
00:04:34.708 --> 00:04:36.472
Are you still dizzy?

63
00:04:36.743 --> 00:04:38.075
I'm all right.

64
00:04:38.145 --> 00:04:40.114
Well. your liver
enzymes are elevated.

65
00:04:40.180 --> 00:04:43.673
And we found traces of a
neurotoxin in your blood.

66
00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:47.278
PHTX3. which usually is
associated with a spider bite.

67
00:04:48.054 --> 00:04:49.265
Lucky you didn't get more of it

68
00:04:49.289 --> 00:04:51.884
or it would have
paralyzed your lungs.

69
00:04:52.492 --> 00:04:55.951
Well. if you feel lightheaded
or feverish. come on back.

70
00:04:57.731 --> 00:04:58.892
Right.

71
00:05:02.903 --> 00:05:04.447
HANK: <i>They find
anything wrong with you?</i>

72
00:05:04.471 --> 00:05:05.962
Just a few toxins in the blood.

73
00:05:06.039 --> 00:05:08.133
Just a few toxins? Like
the kind that can kill you?

74
00:05:08.775 --> 00:05:10.073
Well. apparently not.

75
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:11.805
You gonna be okay?

76
00:05:12.112 --> 00:05:13.136
How do I look?

77
00:05:13.213 --> 00:05:14.841
Like a cop who's
been working all night.

78
00:05:14.915 --> 00:05:16.559
Oh. that's funny. Hank.
That's how you look.

79
00:05:16.583 --> 00:05:18.552
Well. then you look good.

80
00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:22.148
Marie?

81
00:05:22.556 --> 00:05:24.081
She's not stable.

82
00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:25.750
We can't allow
anyone in the ICU yet.

83
00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:27.136
Well. when can I talk to her?

84
00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:28.594
After we're done
running the tests.

85
00:05:30.297 --> 00:05:32.493
We can't risk letting
her slip back into a coma.

86
00:05:33.233 --> 00:05:36.067
I'll call you the minute
we know something.

87
00:05:41.608 --> 00:05:44.237
ID anyone who wants
access to the room.

88
00:05:46.947 --> 00:05:48.108
How is she?

89
00:05:48.181 --> 00:05:49.479
Well. she came out of the coma

90
00:05:49.549 --> 00:05:50.949
but they're still running tests.

91
00:05:51.418 --> 00:05:52.750
So when did the attack happen?

92
00:05:52.819 --> 00:05:54.617
About ten minutes
after I got here.

93
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:57.886
She came up behind me.
she had a syringe in her hand.

94
00:05:58.592 --> 00:05:59.952
How do you know
she wasn't a nurse?

95
00:06:00.093 --> 00:06:02.062
Well. she stuck a needle
in me and she ran away.

96
00:06:03.563 --> 00:06:05.088
Well. you think you
can identify her?

97
00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:06.576
Yeah. she should be
on the security tapes.

98
00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:07.643
I grabbed them when I got here.

99
00:06:07.667 --> 00:06:09.045
They're on their
way to the precinct.

100
00:06:09.069 --> 00:06:10.833
Let's take a look
at those tapes.

101
00:06:10.904 --> 00:06:13.897
If we got another killer on our
hands. we better get on this.

102
00:06:14.608 --> 00:06:17.407
WOMAN OVER P.A.:
<i>Respiratory therapist to 342.</i>

103
00:06:17.477 --> 00:06:20.106
<i>Respiratory therapist
on call to 342.</i>

104
00:06:27.821 --> 00:06:29.821
When's the last time you
saw your aunt before this?

105
00:06:29.890 --> 00:06:32.724
Not for a couple years. I don't
know what she's been up to.

106
00:06:37.030 --> 00:06:38.030
That's her.

107
00:06:39.766 --> 00:06:40.859
Was she alone?

108
00:06:41.201 --> 00:06:42.829
She's the only one I saw.

109
00:06:42.903 --> 00:06:45.134
It would be difficult to
make an ID from the back.

110
00:06:45.205 --> 00:06:46.833
Is this all you got? Yeah.

111
00:06:48.642 --> 00:06:52.101
Well. let me know if you get
something we can work with.

112
00:06:53.013 --> 00:06:55.278
Dude. what did your aunt
do to piss off so many people?

113
00:06:55.548 --> 00:06:56.988
Work for the government
or something?

114
00:06:57.017 --> 00:06:59.919
I had a DUI out on Highway
Two about an hour ago.

115
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:01.687
Driver's got some crazy story

116
00:07:01.755 --> 00:07:04.657
about her boyfriend being
attacked. name's Gilda Darner.

117
00:07:10.230 --> 00:07:11.562
What do you think?

118
00:07:11.631 --> 00:07:13.190
Grown up way too fast.

119
00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:15.394
single parent if she has any.

120
00:07:15.468 --> 00:07:19.997
takes way too many chances and looks
for excitement in all the wrong places.

121
00:07:20.073 --> 00:07:21.564
Sounds like me.

122
00:07:21.641 --> 00:07:23.200
Yeah. Look how you turned out.

123
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:24.775
(CHUCKLES)

124
00:07:27.814 --> 00:07:28.873
Gilda Darner?

125
00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:43.161
This is the house. This
is where it happened.

126
00:07:43.596 --> 00:07:45.656
HANK: Somebody
got here before us.

127
00:07:47.734 --> 00:07:49.862
Stay in the car.

128
00:07:54.874 --> 00:07:55.933
What are you doing here?

129
00:07:56.009 --> 00:07:57.568
I haven't even called it in yet.

130
00:07:57.644 --> 00:07:59.237
What do you got?

131
00:07:59.546 --> 00:08:00.844
Breaking and entering.

132
00:08:01.014 --> 00:08:03.779
Mr. and Mrs. Rabe got back
from Seattle a couple of hours ago.

133
00:08:03.850 --> 00:08:05.785
found their house broken into.

134
00:08:05.852 --> 00:08:06.979
Somebody raided the fridge.

135
00:08:07.053 --> 00:08:08.798
hit the liquor cabinet.
tried on some clothes

136
00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:10.347
and test-drove a couple of beds.

137
00:08:10.423 --> 00:08:11.891
Any sign of violence?
SERGEANT: No.

138
00:08:11.958 --> 00:08:13.551
No blood. No body parts.

139
00:08:13.626 --> 00:08:16.152
Only stains we've come up
with are wine and whoopee.

140
00:08:16.229 --> 00:08:17.356
Who's her missing boy toy?

141
00:08:17.430 --> 00:08:18.728
Says his name's Rocky.

142
00:08:18.798 --> 00:08:22.257
Still trying to figure out
how much of her story is true.

143
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:24.895
Well. she's copping to the
B and E. so some of it is.

144
00:08:25.238 --> 00:08:27.469
Where are the owners? Upstairs.

145
00:08:29.309 --> 00:08:31.642
Somebody was
sleeping in our bed.

146
00:08:31.878 --> 00:08:34.939
Sleep had nothing to do with
what they were doing in our bed.

147
00:08:35.015 --> 00:08:36.984
HANK: You have an alarm system?

148
00:08:37.050 --> 00:08:39.576
Well. we've been a
little lax in using it lately.

149
00:08:39.652 --> 00:08:40.881
We're pretty remote out here.

150
00:08:40.954 --> 00:08:43.150
I mean we've never
had a problem before.

151
00:08:44.624 --> 00:08:46.855
You should see the living room.

152
00:08:48.194 --> 00:08:49.924
Nothing was stolen?

153
00:08:50.997 --> 00:08:53.398
I don't know yet.
Nothing obvious.

154
00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:56.355
HANK: You have
quite a collection.

155
00:08:57.470 --> 00:08:59.462
Is that a Fijian war club?

156
00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:01.804
Yes. actually it is.

157
00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.639
And a New Guinea tribal fork.

158
00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:05.110
This is some valuable stuff.

159
00:09:05.178 --> 00:09:06.646
You know your aboriginal art.

160
00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:08.644
I've never seen
one like that before.

161
00:09:08.815 --> 00:09:11.979
DIANE: It's Germanic. very
rare. from about 900 A.D.

162
00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:16.178
We belong to organizations that
protect native land from development.

163
00:09:16.456 --> 00:09:18.584
There's a lot of rich cultural
heritage disappearing

164
00:09:18.658 --> 00:09:21.321
and we're trying to protect
what's left. both locally and globally.

165
00:09:21.394 --> 00:09:23.795
Honey. I think you're
getting a little irrelevant.

166
00:09:24.297 --> 00:09:26.994
Well. you have to respect
your ancestors. Right. Detective?

167
00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:31.103
I had to respect mine. otherwise
I couldn't sit down for a week.

168
00:09:32.806 --> 00:09:35.173
Anyone else have access to
the house when you were away?

169
00:09:35.241 --> 00:09:36.641
Just our cleaning people.

170
00:09:36.743 --> 00:09:38.837
And our son. Barry.
who's staying with friends.

171
00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:40.489
And our neighbors. the Colberts.

172
00:09:40.513 --> 00:09:44.416
who check on our house from
time to time when we're out of town.

173
00:09:47.687 --> 00:09:49.349
"Fijian war club"?

174
00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:51.152
Second wife was
an anthropologist.

175
00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:53.689
NICK: So there were
two people in that house?

176
00:09:54.194 --> 00:09:55.355
So where's Gilda's boyfriend?

177
00:09:55.428 --> 00:09:58.227
My guess. Rocky's home
right now sleeping it off.

178
00:09:58.898 --> 00:10:00.799
(LOW GROWL)

179
00:10:15.748 --> 00:10:17.080
(GROANING)

180
00:10:22.522 --> 00:10:24.150
(ROCKY SCREAMING)

181
00:10:36.536 --> 00:10:38.528
So you do this for kicks?

182
00:10:38.972 --> 00:10:40.838
Break into homes. party hard?

183
00:10:40.907 --> 00:10:42.136
We were just having fun!

184
00:10:42.208 --> 00:10:43.574
Illegal fun. (SIGHS)

185
00:10:43.910 --> 00:10:47.745
Gilda. you said after you dropped out
of the window you heard Rocky scream.

186
00:10:47.814 --> 00:10:50.374
you started running away from the
house and something chased you?

187
00:10:50.450 --> 00:10:51.509
Yes.

188
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:54.715
It's my fault.

189
00:10:55.922 --> 00:10:57.914
I shoulda gone back for him but

190
00:10:59.292 --> 00:11:01.158
I just left him there.

191
00:11:02.061 --> 00:11:03.359
I left him there.

192
00:11:04.631 --> 00:11:08.193
Please. Please. you've
gotta do something.

193
00:11:16.609 --> 00:11:18.077
(DOOR CLOSES)

194
00:11:22.315 --> 00:11:24.614
Gilda. do you have any
idea who was chasing you?

195
00:11:25.118 --> 00:11:26.882
A man? A dog?

196
00:11:29.222 --> 00:11:30.417
Some kind of animal?

197
00:11:30.657 --> 00:11:32.319
I... I don't know.

198
00:11:33.426 --> 00:11:34.519
I don't know.

199
00:11:34.961 --> 00:11:36.589
I couldn't really
get a good look at it.

200
00:11:36.663 --> 00:11:39.827
I was so scared I just
wanted to get out of there.

201
00:11:43.803 --> 00:11:47.604
I know that something
terrible has happened to him.

202
00:11:56.816 --> 00:11:58.656
They went to Rocky's
house. Rocky wasn't there.

203
00:11:58.718 --> 00:12:00.778
We talked to his
dad. truck driver.

204
00:12:00.853 --> 00:12:03.220
just got back night before
last. hasn't seen Rocky.

205
00:12:03.289 --> 00:12:05.190
What about his mother?
Died when he was a kid.

206
00:12:05.258 --> 00:12:07.159
Did he have a cell
phone? Used to.

207
00:12:07.627 --> 00:12:09.528
Dad said they had to cut
back on expenses so...

208
00:12:09.596 --> 00:12:11.316
Did he have any idea
where his son might be?

209
00:12:11.364 --> 00:12:13.475
He said if you find his
pick-up. that's where he'll be.

210
00:12:13.499 --> 00:12:14.810
Well. his truck's
already been impounded.

211
00:12:14.834 --> 00:12:17.133
Gilda was driving it last night.

212
00:12:17.904 --> 00:12:19.532
That's all I got.

213
00:12:22.842 --> 00:12:24.386
What if their little
party got out of hand.

214
00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:26.402
Rocky got hurt. maybe
he fell down the stairs?

215
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:29.044
Maybe Gilda pushed
him. broke his neck.

216
00:12:29.115 --> 00:12:30.208
Gilda got scared.

217
00:12:30.283 --> 00:12:32.309
Dumped his body in a
river or into the woods.

218
00:12:32.385 --> 00:12:34.196
Now she's trying to make
it look like she's innocent.

219
00:12:34.220 --> 00:12:35.831
I don't think she's trying
to cover anything up.

220
00:12:35.855 --> 00:12:38.654
It seems to me she's
pushing us to find him.

221
00:12:38.725 --> 00:12:41.490
I think we have to take another
look at that house they broke into.

222
00:12:41.561 --> 00:12:43.325
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

223
00:12:45.131 --> 00:12:46.292
Hello?

224
00:12:46.666 --> 00:12:48.328
I need to see you.

225
00:12:49.002 --> 00:12:50.061
Now.

226
00:12:50.403 --> 00:12:54.568
She's very weak. but I realize
you may not have much time.

227
00:12:56.309 --> 00:12:58.175
I'll be right outside.

228
00:13:08.655 --> 00:13:10.248
I was afraid I'd lost you.

229
00:13:10.657 --> 00:13:11.818
Not yet.

230
00:13:12.425 --> 00:13:14.326
You're all I have left.

231
00:13:16.062 --> 00:13:17.182
I don't want this to happen.

232
00:13:17.463 --> 00:13:18.658
I know.

233
00:13:19.866 --> 00:13:21.357
But you'll be all right.

234
00:13:21.434 --> 00:13:23.062
I don't feel like I'm
gonna be all right.

235
00:13:23.903 --> 00:13:25.872
I'm still trying to make
sense of everything.

236
00:13:27.006 --> 00:13:29.601
If you hadn't been here. I
would have lost my mind.

237
00:13:31.010 --> 00:13:32.535
And I'm not sure I haven't.

238
00:13:32.779 --> 00:13:34.179
Don't doubt yourself.

239
00:13:34.781 --> 00:13:36.147
I've seen so much.

240
00:13:36.215 --> 00:13:37.547
And you'll see more.

241
00:13:38.551 --> 00:13:40.986
You have a responsibility
that you cannot ignore.

242
00:13:41.721 --> 00:13:43.189
I couldn't ignore
it if I tried it.

243
00:13:44.624 --> 00:13:47.059
You have to hunt
down the bad ones.

244
00:13:47.794 --> 00:13:49.524
Just like your ancestors did.

245
00:13:50.229 --> 00:13:52.164
There's a reason
that you're a cop.

246
00:13:52.231 --> 00:13:54.530
You have an ability
and you must use it.

247
00:13:55.401 --> 00:13:56.994
no matter what happens to me.

248
00:13:58.204 --> 00:14:00.173
I'll go get a doctor. No.

249
00:14:02.375 --> 00:14:04.071
The Reapers followed me here.

250
00:14:04.610 --> 00:14:05.850
That means there could be more.

251
00:14:06.179 --> 00:14:07.442
How many are there?

252
00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:08.537
Nobody knows.

253
00:14:09.716 --> 00:14:12.151
They're a secret organization
dedicated to killing us.

254
00:14:12.452 --> 00:14:14.011
You mean Grimms?

255
00:14:14.087 --> 00:14:15.282
There are more like us?

256
00:14:15.355 --> 00:14:16.414
Yes.

257
00:14:16.923 --> 00:14:18.283
But I don't have
contact with them.

258
00:14:18.558 --> 00:14:19.868
What about the things
that I've been seeing?

259
00:14:19.892 --> 00:14:21.326
How many more
of those are there?

260
00:14:21.394 --> 00:14:23.274
There are more in the
books than I've ever seen.

261
00:14:24.797 --> 00:14:27.665
You must not let the trailer be
found. They don't know it exists.

262
00:14:28.468 --> 00:14:29.468
(GASPING)

263
00:14:29.535 --> 00:14:32.403
I hope I haven't done more
harm than good by coming to you.

264
00:14:32.705 --> 00:14:34.230
(MACHINE BEEPS)

265
00:14:34.574 --> 00:14:35.837
(GASPING)

266
00:14:36.976 --> 00:14:39.571
Let her rest. You
can come back later.

267
00:14:39.645 --> 00:14:40.908
(MACHINES BEEPING RAPIDLY)

268
00:14:43.883 --> 00:14:45.647
(BEEPING STABILIZES)

269
00:14:45.952 --> 00:14:47.750
(VEHICLE DOOR OPENING)

270
00:14:50.923 --> 00:14:52.186
How is she?

271
00:14:52.258 --> 00:14:53.385
Well. she's dying of cancer

272
00:14:53.459 --> 00:14:55.291
and she's had two
attempts made at her life.

273
00:14:55.361 --> 00:14:57.956
Other than that
she's doing all right.

274
00:15:00.867 --> 00:15:02.233
She's one tough lady.

275
00:15:02.301 --> 00:15:03.792
I had no idea.

276
00:15:04.270 --> 00:15:05.795
So you got anything
on the Rabes?

277
00:15:05.872 --> 00:15:08.740
Yeah. Their house
sits on about 200 acres.

278
00:15:08.975 --> 00:15:10.841
backs up onto
the national forest.

279
00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:12.776
Five hundred square
miles of trees behind them.

280
00:15:12.845 --> 00:15:14.507
Lots of places for
Rocky to get lost.

281
00:15:14.614 --> 00:15:16.412
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

282
00:15:17.183 --> 00:15:19.345
These woods are too
big for the two of us.

283
00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:21.650
Let's get some people out here.

284
00:15:26.893 --> 00:15:28.413
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. Look out.

285
00:15:28.728 --> 00:15:29.923
(TIRES SCREECHING)

286
00:15:52.385 --> 00:15:53.444
Hey.

287
00:15:54.587 --> 00:15:55.987
Nice riding.

288
00:15:56.222 --> 00:15:57.554
Oh. I hope we didn't scare you.

289
00:15:58.057 --> 00:16:00.017
Oh. no. You guys are
lucky you didn't get thumped.

290
00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:01.573
Look. we knew
what we were doing.

291
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:04.306
That's a good thing 'cause I
hate cleaning blood off my car.

292
00:16:04.330 --> 00:16:06.765
You guys here for my parents?

293
00:16:07.066 --> 00:16:09.035
Detectives
Burkhardt and Griffin.

294
00:16:09.202 --> 00:16:11.899
You're Barry Rabe.
You live here. right?

295
00:16:14.006 --> 00:16:15.406
You guys ever
seen either of them?

296
00:16:17.443 --> 00:16:18.706
Oh. no. take your time.

297
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:22.312
Make sure you don't know
them from school or anything.

298
00:16:22.381 --> 00:16:23.725
Look. we've never
seen them before.

299
00:16:23.749 --> 00:16:25.945
Boys. dinner's ready. Wash up.

300
00:16:26.419 --> 00:16:27.580
What are you doing back here?

301
00:16:27.854 --> 00:16:29.550
Did you find out who
broke into our house?

302
00:16:29.622 --> 00:16:30.646
Yeah. I think so.

303
00:16:31.157 --> 00:16:32.489
Frank. you should come out here.

304
00:16:32.725 --> 00:16:35.194
Ma'am. can you
take a look at these?

305
00:16:35.261 --> 00:16:36.422
The girl's already in custody

306
00:16:36.496 --> 00:16:38.795
but we haven't seen the guy yet.

307
00:16:38.998 --> 00:16:41.593
Have you ever seen
either of these guys?

308
00:16:42.735 --> 00:16:43.759
No.

309
00:16:43.936 --> 00:16:44.936
Me either.

310
00:16:45.471 --> 00:16:47.783
Hey. Barry. you didn't happen
to come home last night. did you?

311
00:16:47.807 --> 00:16:51.209
He was staying at Jason and
T.B.'s house while we were gone.

312
00:16:51.277 --> 00:16:54.111
Sorry. Mrs. Rabe. We have to ask.
just in case he saw the boy leave.

313
00:16:54.647 --> 00:16:56.309
No. I didn't get home
until this morning.

314
00:16:56.749 --> 00:16:58.149
after my parents got back.

315
00:17:00.253 --> 00:17:01.516
(GULPING)

316
00:17:03.256 --> 00:17:05.248
No. I... I didn't see him.

317
00:17:05.858 --> 00:17:07.292
How far away do you guys live?

318
00:17:07.393 --> 00:17:08.393
What is this?

319
00:17:09.228 --> 00:17:11.640
Look. we're just trying to figure
out where everybody was last night.

320
00:17:11.664 --> 00:17:12.841
We know they
broke into your house

321
00:17:12.865 --> 00:17:14.545
but no one's seen the
boy since last night.

322
00:17:14.634 --> 00:17:17.502
The girl said she heard a scream
inside the house after she left.

323
00:17:17.570 --> 00:17:21.405
And you believe someone who broke into
our house. drank our wine. ate our food.

324
00:17:21.474 --> 00:17:23.272
and took advantage
of our bedroom?

325
00:17:23.876 --> 00:17:26.311
I think you'd be better off
looking under a few rocks.

326
00:17:26.946 --> 00:17:29.882
I wish you'd remember
that we're the victims here.

327
00:17:29.949 --> 00:17:32.043
Boys. let's go in the house.

328
00:17:34.587 --> 00:17:38.524
If you wanna talk to me you can
call me tomorrow at my law firm.

329
00:17:42.528 --> 00:17:45.020
Man. we really hit a nerve.

330
00:17:50.937 --> 00:17:53.657
Let's run some phone records. pin
down where everyone was last night.

331
00:18:10.656 --> 00:18:11.988
She came out of the coma.

332
00:18:12.058 --> 00:18:13.390
And I've had to
put guards on her.

333
00:18:13.659 --> 00:18:14.718
What do you want me to do?

334
00:18:14.794 --> 00:18:16.505
We can't allow her to
tell him anything more.

335
00:18:16.529 --> 00:18:17.588
We need him with us.

336
00:18:17.663 --> 00:18:18.687
Then how do I get to her?

337
00:18:18.764 --> 00:18:20.357
Well. you don't.

338
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.091
But you get somebody who can.

339
00:18:22.168 --> 00:18:23.363
With guards on her?

340
00:18:23.436 --> 00:18:24.460
Don't worry about that.

341
00:18:24.537 --> 00:18:27.701
Just find the right people.
and I do mean people.

342
00:18:28.040 --> 00:18:29.318
We can't afford
someone getting excited

343
00:18:29.342 --> 00:18:30.503
and blowing the whole thing.

344
00:18:32.244 --> 00:18:33.906
Don't you know this is
a bad neighborhood?

345
00:18:34.547 --> 00:18:36.641
How much is it worth
for you not to get hurt?

346
00:18:37.149 --> 00:18:39.641
Don't worry. I'll
take care of this.

347
00:18:40.186 --> 00:18:41.415
(SNARLS)

348
00:18:44.156 --> 00:18:45.681
(MAN SCREAMING)

349
00:18:51.430 --> 00:18:52.955
(DOOR OPENING)

350
00:18:53.432 --> 00:18:54.957
JULIETTE: Nick?

351
00:18:55.134 --> 00:18:56.693
NICK: Yeah. in here.
(DOOR CLOSING)

352
00:18:58.137 --> 00:19:01.733
I picked up Chinese
from Lotus. and

353
00:19:02.575 --> 00:19:03.599
got Voodoo donuts.

354
00:19:03.676 --> 00:19:04.803
Oh. you're the best.

355
00:19:04.877 --> 00:19:06.277
Don't be such a cop.

356
00:19:06.345 --> 00:19:08.439
The donuts are for dessert.

357
00:19:11.784 --> 00:19:13.116
Are we buying a totem pole?

358
00:19:14.186 --> 00:19:17.315
No. I saw one outside a
house of a case I'm working on.

359
00:19:17.390 --> 00:19:19.120
It's some kind of
clan of the bear.

360
00:19:19.191 --> 00:19:21.626
"The bear is a messenger
to the supernatural world.

361
00:19:21.694 --> 00:19:24.926
"His position of dominance
in the totemic hierarchy

362
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:26.932
"is the result of a
common ancestral belief

363
00:19:26.999 --> 00:19:29.264
"in the sanctity
of their territory."

364
00:19:29.335 --> 00:19:32.066
Hmm. Is the totem
pole some kind of clue?

365
00:19:32.738 --> 00:19:35.731
I don't know. but you
make it sound kinda sexy.

366
00:19:36.709 --> 00:19:38.769
It's just the word
pole. Mmm-hmm.

367
00:19:40.813 --> 00:19:42.748
I stopped by to see Marie today.

368
00:19:43.416 --> 00:19:45.544
It scared me seeing all
the police in the hospital.

369
00:19:45.618 --> 00:19:48.110
I don't know why anybody
would want to hurt her.

370
00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:50.281
She can't even die in peace.

371
00:19:51.757 --> 00:19:52.952
How you doing with all that?

372
00:19:53.159 --> 00:19:57.062
Well. I'm not doing too good about it.
but. you know. there's nothing I can do.

373
00:19:57.129 --> 00:19:59.564
So I'm putting on my happy face.

374
00:19:59.899 --> 00:20:02.061
I'm not buying that
grin. Put it back.

375
00:20:21.253 --> 00:20:22.949
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

376
00:20:38.704 --> 00:20:40.263
Okay. Do it.

377
00:20:41.006 --> 00:20:42.006
(GRUNTING)

378
00:20:44.110 --> 00:20:45.339
Ah! That'll work.

379
00:20:59.091 --> 00:21:00.184
(DOOR OPENING)

380
00:21:06.799 --> 00:21:09.234
Aunt Marie? What
are you doing here?

381
00:21:10.536 --> 00:21:12.505
Remember what I told you.

382
00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:15.633
Okay.

383
00:21:19.145 --> 00:21:20.340
There will be more red...

384
00:21:26.886 --> 00:21:28.445
when the sun goes down.

385
00:21:39.598 --> 00:21:40.598
(GRUNTING)

386
00:21:40.866 --> 00:21:42.129
(GASPING)

387
00:21:43.235 --> 00:21:44.498
You okay?

388
00:21:46.906 --> 00:21:51.173
Yeah. Yeah. just
a... A bad dream.

389
00:21:51.277 --> 00:21:52.575
I hope. What was it?

390
00:21:56.415 --> 00:21:59.817
My aunt just stabbed
me in the hand.

391
00:22:00.319 --> 00:22:02.220
What did you do to her?

392
00:22:03.689 --> 00:22:05.214
Nope. just a dream.

393
00:22:05.291 --> 00:22:08.193
But I don't even know where
to begin interpreting that one.

394
00:22:08.260 --> 00:22:11.628
I was trying to let you
sleep. A lot of good that did.

395
00:22:15.968 --> 00:22:18.563
Hey. hey. Where're
you going so early?

396
00:22:19.872 --> 00:22:23.331
I'm operating on a bulldog
at 7:00. I'll call you later.

397
00:23:10.656 --> 00:23:12.454
MARIE: <i>You have to
hunt down the bad ones.</i>

398
00:23:27.339 --> 00:23:28.864
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

399
00:23:39.251 --> 00:23:41.015
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

400
00:23:42.187 --> 00:23:43.382
(SIGHS)

401
00:23:46.425 --> 00:23:47.449
We need to talk.

402
00:23:47.526 --> 00:23:50.018
Not at 6:30 in the
morning we don't.

403
00:23:50.963 --> 00:23:52.056
This is important.

404
00:23:52.131 --> 00:23:56.967
Oh. well. come on in. then. Have a
cup of coffee. Bagel? Cream cheese?

405
00:23:57.870 --> 00:24:01.068
First I wanna thank you for
helping me out with the kidnapping.

406
00:24:01.607 --> 00:24:03.576
A gift basket
would've been nice.

407
00:24:03.642 --> 00:24:04.753
How long is this gonna take?

408
00:24:04.777 --> 00:24:07.611
I'm right in the middle
of my Pilates. man.

409
00:24:07.780 --> 00:24:08.873
You ever seen one of these?

410
00:24:16.188 --> 00:24:18.089
Not up close. thank God.

411
00:24:20.726 --> 00:24:23.389
I think Jagerbars use
these for disemboweling.

412
00:24:23.963 --> 00:24:25.488
Now I'm hungry.

413
00:24:26.665 --> 00:24:28.065
Sure you don't want a bagel?

414
00:24:28.133 --> 00:24:29.678
I'm gonna French
press some coffee. too.

415
00:24:29.702 --> 00:24:30.795
Guatemalan Highlands.

416
00:24:30.869 --> 00:24:32.895
Craft-Roasted. Very robust.

417
00:24:34.673 --> 00:24:35.717
What do you know
about Jagerbars?

418
00:24:35.741 --> 00:24:37.676
What am I. your
personal Grimmopedia?

419
00:24:37.743 --> 00:24:38.938
No. you're a Blutbad.

420
00:24:39.011 --> 00:24:42.641
and I'm assuming that
Blutbad know about Jagerbaden.

421
00:24:42.982 --> 00:24:44.746
It's just Jagerbars.

422
00:24:45.551 --> 00:24:46.951
You see them like
I see them. right?

423
00:24:47.353 --> 00:24:48.353
Yes.

424
00:24:49.588 --> 00:24:51.399
Yeah. I'm just trying to figure
out what I'm up against here.

425
00:24:51.423 --> 00:24:53.654
Okay. right there. Don't
even compare the two.

426
00:24:53.726 --> 00:24:55.922
We don't rummage like they do.

427
00:24:56.729 --> 00:24:58.425
How'd you run across
a Jagerbar anyway?

428
00:24:58.764 --> 00:25:02.098
Look. I'm working on a case
and I saw a kid turn into one.

429
00:25:02.601 --> 00:25:03.864
That where you got the claw?

430
00:25:03.936 --> 00:25:04.960
No. my aunt had it.

431
00:25:05.104 --> 00:25:08.302
Oh. right. her again.
Aunt Marie. right?

432
00:25:08.540 --> 00:25:10.509
Yeah. I couldn't sleep
the last two nights

433
00:25:10.576 --> 00:25:12.602
thinking old Aunt Marie
was gonna cut off my head

434
00:25:12.678 --> 00:25:14.772
and stick it on a lamp post.

435
00:25:15.280 --> 00:25:16.958
That's how my great
grandma ended up. you know.

436
00:25:16.982 --> 00:25:18.575
Hey. she's still
in the hospital.

437
00:25:18.650 --> 00:25:20.585
Oh. Sorry.

438
00:25:21.920 --> 00:25:24.890
They use those
claws in the Roh-Hatz.

439
00:25:25.324 --> 00:25:26.383
Roh-Hatz?

440
00:25:26.458 --> 00:25:28.178
It's like a Bar Mitzvah
for bears. you know.

441
00:25:28.227 --> 00:25:29.286
A Jager Bar Mitzvah.

442
00:25:29.361 --> 00:25:30.659
It's a very physical thing.

443
00:25:30.729 --> 00:25:34.131
A lot of pounding of
chests and like. wailing.

444
00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:35.859
But who wails anymore?

445
00:25:36.001 --> 00:25:39.563
Supposed to connect with
the primitive beast in all of us.

446
00:25:41.874 --> 00:25:44.969
And believe me. I
do mean all of us.

447
00:25:48.180 --> 00:25:49.273
So what do they do?

448
00:25:49.348 --> 00:25:50.748
It's all about the chase.

449
00:25:51.216 --> 00:25:52.240
What chase?

450
00:25:52.317 --> 00:25:54.809
The Roh-Hatz. you know.
Cave man mumbo jumbo.

451
00:25:54.887 --> 00:25:57.652
Let's get some beers and
barbecue and be stupid.

452
00:25:58.290 --> 00:26:00.035
I mean I like to camp
as much as the next guy.

453
00:26:00.059 --> 00:26:02.153
you know. maybe once a year.

454
00:26:02.528 --> 00:26:03.996
You want plain or
onion. I gotta go.

455
00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:07.163
Oh. well. Thanks
for stopping by.

456
00:26:14.573 --> 00:26:16.371
What are you drawing?

457
00:26:23.015 --> 00:26:24.278
Jagerbar.

458
00:26:26.051 --> 00:26:27.451
You saw one?

459
00:26:30.289 --> 00:26:32.884
It was a family. but the
boy's the only one I saw.

460
00:26:32.958 --> 00:26:34.586
How old? Eighteen.

461
00:26:35.928 --> 00:26:38.989
That could be a problem
if they're traditional.

462
00:26:40.032 --> 00:26:41.032
Anyone die?

463
00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:44.397
I don't know. I've
got a missing person.

464
00:26:45.804 --> 00:26:47.084
Do you know what
the Roh-Hatz is?

465
00:26:47.639 --> 00:26:50.199
You're learning. That's good.

466
00:26:53.078 --> 00:26:55.104
It's a rite of passage.
from boy to man.

467
00:26:55.981 --> 00:26:57.779
They do it at sunset.

468
00:26:59.885 --> 00:27:01.478
It isn't pretty.

469
00:27:03.522 --> 00:27:06.583
The red of the sun and
the blood on their hands.

470
00:27:15.067 --> 00:27:16.330
Just got the phone records.

471
00:27:16.401 --> 00:27:18.666
Several calls were made
between 9:00 and midnight.

472
00:27:18.737 --> 00:27:21.070
We triangulated a call made
from Barry Rabe's cell phone

473
00:27:21.140 --> 00:27:23.609
that puts him at his
house at 11:30 that night.

474
00:27:23.675 --> 00:27:24.973
When Gilda was there with Rocky.

475
00:27:25.043 --> 00:27:28.070
Yeah. so Barry's lying and
lawyer dad is running interference.

476
00:27:28.347 --> 00:27:29.815
A lawyer doing a bad thing?

477
00:27:29.882 --> 00:27:30.925
Never heard of that before?

478
00:27:30.949 --> 00:27:32.429
Hey. Nick. can I
talk to you a minute?

479
00:27:32.518 --> 00:27:33.542
Yes. sir.

480
00:27:33.619 --> 00:27:36.064
Listen. I had to pull the guys
guarding your aunt at the hospital.

481
00:27:36.088 --> 00:27:37.112
What?

482
00:27:37.189 --> 00:27:38.266
With no hard evidence
of a second attack

483
00:27:38.290 --> 00:27:39.767
I couldn't justify the
expense to the Chief

484
00:27:39.791 --> 00:27:42.911
without it looking like we're giving
preferential treatment to police families.

485
00:27:44.796 --> 00:27:47.095
I'm sorry but my hands are tied.

486
00:27:56.375 --> 00:27:58.139
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

487
00:28:06.618 --> 00:28:07.813
Monroe.

488
00:28:08.587 --> 00:28:09.850
Now what?

489
00:28:10.455 --> 00:28:11.684
MONROE: (WHISPERING) A Grimm?

490
00:28:12.090 --> 00:28:14.218
Are you out of your
mind? I can't do this.

491
00:28:14.526 --> 00:28:17.360
Look. I just need your help until
I can figure something else out.

492
00:28:17.596 --> 00:28:18.757
I'm not a cop.

493
00:28:19.164 --> 00:28:21.409
Yeah. You're the only one
who knows what I'm dealing with.

494
00:28:21.433 --> 00:28:24.335
No. I am the only one who is
stupid enough to talk to you.

495
00:28:24.636 --> 00:28:25.660
I'll owe you one.

496
00:28:25.737 --> 00:28:27.228
Dude. you already owe me three.

497
00:28:27.306 --> 00:28:28.569
Three? Yeah.

498
00:28:28.640 --> 00:28:30.040
The little girl who
was kidnapped.

499
00:28:30.108 --> 00:28:32.771
the Jagerbar at
6:30 this morning

500
00:28:32.878 --> 00:28:34.506
in the middle of my Pilates.

501
00:28:34.580 --> 00:28:35.673
and now this!

502
00:28:36.815 --> 00:28:38.943
Okay. I'll owe you three.

503
00:28:39.218 --> 00:28:40.361
What the hell makes you think

504
00:28:40.385 --> 00:28:42.354
I am gonna stay
here and protect her?

505
00:28:43.455 --> 00:28:45.219
Because I trust you.

506
00:28:45.624 --> 00:28:46.853
Oh. man.

507
00:28:46.925 --> 00:28:49.417
Look. I'll be back
as soon as I can.

508
00:28:56.802 --> 00:28:58.395
Maybe you shouldn't trust me.

509
00:28:58.637 --> 00:29:00.401
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

510
00:29:00.939 --> 00:29:02.635
What's up? HANK:
<i>Rocky's dad just called.</i>

511
00:29:02.708 --> 00:29:03.732
<i>Gilda made bail.</i>

512
00:29:04.009 --> 00:29:06.387
She went over to his house and
got a gun. Rocky had in his room.

513
00:29:06.411 --> 00:29:07.470
He couldn't stop her.

514
00:29:07.546 --> 00:29:10.482
She said she was gonna get Rocky
back or kill the people that took him.

515
00:29:23.395 --> 00:29:25.125
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

516
00:29:28.567 --> 00:29:29.762
Where is he?

517
00:29:29.835 --> 00:29:31.360
Oh. my God. Where is he?

518
00:29:31.436 --> 00:29:32.847
Are you the girl that
broke into my house?

519
00:29:32.871 --> 00:29:34.772
You tell me where
he is or I'll shoot!

520
00:29:34.840 --> 00:29:37.366
Please don't hurt me. I. I don't
know what you're talking about.

521
00:29:37.442 --> 00:29:38.442
You know where he...

522
00:29:38.510 --> 00:29:39.876
(SCREAMING)

523
00:29:44.683 --> 00:29:45.844
Are you okay. Mom?

524
00:29:47.252 --> 00:29:48.515
I am now.

525
00:29:48.954 --> 00:29:50.513
And well done. Son.

526
00:29:51.323 --> 00:29:53.554
Hunting two is better than one.

527
00:29:54.159 --> 00:29:55.821
You make your ancestors proud.

528
00:29:58.830 --> 00:30:00.162
(GROANING)

529
00:30:00.899 --> 00:30:01.923
Ah!

530
00:30:05.871 --> 00:30:07.669
Get rid of her truck.

531
00:30:09.508 --> 00:30:10.840
(GROWLING)

532
00:30:23.588 --> 00:30:24.612
Hi.

533
00:30:25.557 --> 00:30:26.581
Barry home?

534
00:30:26.658 --> 00:30:28.149
No. he's out with friends.

535
00:30:28.327 --> 00:30:30.228
Doing what? I don't
know. Riding their bikes.

536
00:30:30.295 --> 00:30:31.773
God. I hope he
doesn't break his neck.

537
00:30:31.797 --> 00:30:33.095
(CAR APPROACHING)

538
00:30:39.471 --> 00:30:40.530
What do you want?

539
00:30:40.605 --> 00:30:42.938
The woman who broke into
your house is on her way here.

540
00:30:43.141 --> 00:30:44.973
She's not happy.
She's got a gun.

541
00:30:45.143 --> 00:30:46.805
What? Is everything okay?

542
00:30:46.878 --> 00:30:47.937
Everything's fine.

543
00:30:48.013 --> 00:30:49.057
No. I don't really think so.

544
00:30:49.081 --> 00:30:50.601
Nick. doesn't look
like she's here yet.

545
00:30:50.649 --> 00:30:52.117
I'm going back down the road.

546
00:30:52.184 --> 00:30:54.676
I'll block it off in
case she shows.

547
00:30:56.521 --> 00:30:57.955
We need to talk. Right now.

548
00:30:58.256 --> 00:31:01.590
I know what you are. You know
who I am. So let's cut the crap.

549
00:31:01.860 --> 00:31:03.624
You want to cut the crap?

550
00:31:03.695 --> 00:31:07.826
Okay. you're a Grimm.
You're a danger to my family.

551
00:31:08.433 --> 00:31:10.345
And don't think wearing a
badge is gonna protect you.

552
00:31:10.369 --> 00:31:11.667
This isn't about me.

553
00:31:13.572 --> 00:31:14.870
I know about the hunt.

554
00:31:15.006 --> 00:31:16.086
What are you talking about?

555
00:31:16.274 --> 00:31:17.298
The Roh-Hatz.

556
00:31:17.376 --> 00:31:18.435
Nobody does that anymore.

557
00:31:18.510 --> 00:31:19.569
Yes. they do.

558
00:31:19.644 --> 00:31:21.964
And when the sun goes down
tonight. it's gonna be too late.

559
00:31:22.147 --> 00:31:24.048
Look. Barry and those
two boys have got Rocky.

560
00:31:24.116 --> 00:31:25.396
And we don't have a lot of time.

561
00:31:27.652 --> 00:31:29.644
Come on. you're a lawyer.

562
00:31:29.755 --> 00:31:32.623
If they kill this innocent
kid over this stupid hunt.

563
00:31:32.991 --> 00:31:34.892
their lives are over.

564
00:31:34.960 --> 00:31:36.826
Where are they? I told you.

565
00:31:37.062 --> 00:31:38.394
Where are they?

566
00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:43.696
Why don't you ask
to see his warrant?

567
00:31:44.536 --> 00:31:45.902
Oh. my God.

568
00:31:46.438 --> 00:31:48.066
I didn't realize.

569
00:31:48.540 --> 00:31:49.564
So what do you wanna do?

570
00:31:49.641 --> 00:31:53.100
You wanna go inside. have
a few drinks. forget about it?

571
00:31:53.678 --> 00:31:54.918
Or do you want to come with me?

572
00:31:56.415 --> 00:31:57.508
Okay.

573
00:31:58.316 --> 00:32:00.061
But we're gonna have
to take my four-wheeler.

574
00:32:00.085 --> 00:32:01.280
You know where they are?

575
00:32:01.653 --> 00:32:04.088
I think I know
where they might be.

576
00:32:23.041 --> 00:32:25.772
Requesting backup
at 1534 Wilder Road.

577
00:32:41.426 --> 00:32:44.396
If we find them. promise me
you're not gonna hurt them.

578
00:32:44.463 --> 00:32:45.556
I won't if I don't have to.

579
00:32:46.698 --> 00:32:47.791
Okay.

580
00:32:52.637 --> 00:32:53.900
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

581
00:32:54.940 --> 00:32:56.374
<i>It's Nick. You got anything?</i>

582
00:32:56.441 --> 00:32:58.069
I found the truck.
She's here somewhere.

583
00:32:58.143 --> 00:32:59.921
<i>I'm with Frank Rabe.
I'm going after the boys.</i>

584
00:32:59.945 --> 00:33:01.641
<i>I'll call you if I get anything.</i>

585
00:33:01.813 --> 00:33:03.213
(SOBBING) (GRUNTING)

586
00:33:12.224 --> 00:33:15.251
We're sorry we broke into your
house. We'll never do it again.

587
00:33:18.096 --> 00:33:19.826
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

588
00:33:27.639 --> 00:33:29.733
(GRUNTING) Just let her go.

589
00:33:29.808 --> 00:33:30.969
Yeah. we'll let her go.

590
00:33:31.176 --> 00:33:32.296
We're gonna let you go. too.

591
00:33:32.644 --> 00:33:34.636
Don't worry. We'll
give you a head start.

592
00:33:34.846 --> 00:33:37.441
No! Please! No!

593
00:33:38.149 --> 00:33:41.051
Oh. man. You're really scared.

594
00:33:41.119 --> 00:33:42.212
(SOBBING)

595
00:33:42.354 --> 00:33:44.084
This is ridiculous.

596
00:33:51.429 --> 00:33:53.557
You people murdered
my grandfather.

597
00:33:53.999 --> 00:33:56.093
The Grimms burned down his farm.

598
00:33:56.468 --> 00:33:59.199
cut off his head. his
hands and his feet.

599
00:33:59.304 --> 00:34:02.706
Okay. now he deserved it
for some of the things he did.

600
00:34:02.774 --> 00:34:04.242
But if my parents
could see me now.

601
00:34:04.342 --> 00:34:07.244
standing this close to you
and not avenging the family.

602
00:34:07.979 --> 00:34:10.574
last Thanksgiving I'd be
invited to. I can tell you that.

603
00:34:16.187 --> 00:34:18.315
Take your best shot. Blutbad.

604
00:34:33.038 --> 00:34:34.700
We have to take
the trail from here.

605
00:34:34.773 --> 00:34:36.053
How do you know
they'll be there?

606
00:34:36.241 --> 00:34:37.470
I don't.

607
00:35:03.501 --> 00:35:04.799
(GRUNTING)

608
00:35:05.470 --> 00:35:06.802
(GROANING)

609
00:35:18.950 --> 00:35:20.282
(SNARLING)

610
00:35:25.624 --> 00:35:26.956
(GROANING)

611
00:35:31.229 --> 00:35:32.595
(SCREAMING)

612
00:35:33.765 --> 00:35:35.097
(GROWLING)

613
00:35:38.903 --> 00:35:41.236
Okay. that went
a little too far.

614
00:35:52.984 --> 00:35:54.953
There's a cave up ahead.

615
00:36:01.593 --> 00:36:03.473
Let me go first and try
and talk them out of it.

616
00:36:04.462 --> 00:36:05.486
No!

617
00:36:06.331 --> 00:36:08.391
I'm either coming with
you or I'm going alone.

618
00:36:29.721 --> 00:36:30.882
We're too late.

619
00:36:36.194 --> 00:36:37.526
(GROWLING)

620
00:36:39.197 --> 00:36:40.756
It's started.

621
00:36:45.170 --> 00:36:46.502
(GROWLING)

622
00:36:47.005 --> 00:36:48.496
(BOTH PANTING)

623
00:36:52.510 --> 00:36:53.876
Ah! Get up!

624
00:36:58.683 --> 00:36:59.742
(GROWLING)

625
00:37:21.406 --> 00:37:22.635
Get out!

626
00:37:24.242 --> 00:37:25.574
(GRUNTING)

627
00:37:29.247 --> 00:37:30.306
(FIRES)

628
00:37:31.116 --> 00:37:33.176
This isn't gonna get any
better unless you stop.

629
00:37:33.585 --> 00:37:36.885
No! Barry! Son! This is over.

630
00:37:38.423 --> 00:37:39.423
ROCKY: Stay down.

631
00:37:40.725 --> 00:37:42.250
This stops now.

632
00:37:43.661 --> 00:37:44.788
No!

633
00:37:46.030 --> 00:37:47.623
Mom! Don't!

634
00:37:49.634 --> 00:37:51.034
(SCREECHING)

635
00:37:52.237 --> 00:37:54.103
(CONTINUES SCREECHING)

636
00:38:13.725 --> 00:38:15.887
Mom? Mom?

637
00:38:16.261 --> 00:38:18.253
Please. I am so sorry.

638
00:38:19.197 --> 00:38:20.495
You did nothing wrong.

639
00:38:21.132 --> 00:38:24.500
Yeah. he did. Diane. And now
we're all gonna have to pay for it.

640
00:38:25.537 --> 00:38:27.904
You have to respect
your ancestors.

641
00:38:28.640 --> 00:38:29.938
Not like this.

642
00:38:44.489 --> 00:38:45.582
Okay. Let's see.

643
00:38:45.657 --> 00:38:49.059
We got kidnapping and attempted
murder for Barry. Jason. and T.B.

644
00:38:49.127 --> 00:38:50.767
Breaking and entering
for Rocky and Gilda.

645
00:38:51.362 --> 00:38:53.558
Well. at least they
weren't doing drugs.

646
00:38:53.631 --> 00:38:54.963
Detective?

647
00:38:58.436 --> 00:39:00.302
She wanted them to
know their heritage.

648
00:39:01.239 --> 00:39:03.174
She never understood
the danger of it.

649
00:39:04.442 --> 00:39:07.037
It isn't easy to give
up your history.

650
00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:10.539
You haven't had
to give up yours.

651
00:39:11.082 --> 00:39:13.210
Yeah. it's been a lot of fun.

652
00:39:13.685 --> 00:39:15.449
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

653
00:39:16.321 --> 00:39:17.321
Hello?

654
00:39:17.388 --> 00:39:19.619
Look. you told me to
protect her and I did.

655
00:39:19.691 --> 00:39:24.129
But. I think I may have
gone a little overboard.

656
00:39:24.495 --> 00:39:27.192
WOMAN OVER P.A.: <i>Trauma
surgeon to OR one. stat.</i>

657
00:39:27.265 --> 00:39:28.961
<i>Trauma surgeon to OR one. stat.</i>

658
00:39:29.033 --> 00:39:31.378
Look. I can't stick around.
Things are getting a little dicey.

659
00:39:31.402 --> 00:39:34.099
You should get down here.
I'm not sure I got all of them.

660
00:40:03.234 --> 00:40:04.293
(MACHINE BEEPING)

661
00:40:04.836 --> 00:40:06.361
(BOTH GRUNTING)

662
00:40:06.804 --> 00:40:08.500
MALE NURSE:
Get security up here!

663
00:40:09.741 --> 00:40:10.741
(BOTH GRUNTING)

664
00:40:18.349 --> 00:40:19.874
(GROANS SOFTLY)

665
00:40:26.124 --> 00:40:27.183
(PANTING)

666
00:40:31.763 --> 00:40:33.356
Remember who you are.

667
00:40:33.598 --> 00:40:36.591
Trust your instincts
and nothing else.

668
00:40:41.005 --> 00:40:42.268
(GASPING)

669
00:40:47.512 --> 00:40:48.673
Marie?

670
00:40:52.317 --> 00:40:53.546
Come on.

671
00:41:33.024 --> 00:41:34.253
Goodbye.

672
00:41:38.096 --> 00:41:39.428
Rest well.

673
00:41:41.032 --> 00:41:42.159
Are you all right?

674
00:41:42.567 --> 00:41:43.933
(SNIFFLING)

675
00:41:44.068 --> 00:41:45.092
No.

676
00:41:54.278 --> 00:41:55.769
But I will be.

676
00:41:56.305 --> 00:42:56.244
